<h1 id="english">What's up <%= @user.username %>?</h1>

<p>Congrats! Your request to manage <%= @band.name %> has been approved by our moderators. You can now edit your bands information at anytime by clicking ‘edit this band’ at the very bottom of your band’s profile page (please note, you must be logged in to see this option). To see a list of all the events / venues / band profiles you manage, simply log in and go to ‘Your Page’ (under ‘account’ in the main menu, again you must be logged in to see this). Make sure to keep your band profile up to date so your fans (both new and old) know where to find you and what you are up to. </p>


<p>As a user of DoIndie you can also add all your upcoming shows to our show calendar by simply logging in and submitting your gig details here :  <a href="http://doindie.co.kr/events/new">http://doindie.co.kr/events/new</a>. It takes just a few short minutes to create an event on DoIndie. We have thousands of visitors to our site every month. So what are you waiting for, submit your show and get promoting now ;)</p>

<p>We now have a ‘fan profile’ feature on DoIndie, where your fans will be able to follow you band. People who ‘like’ your band on DoIndie will be able to keep up to date with all your gigs in their own personalized gig calendar. For now, our ‘fan profiles’ simply offer users a personalized gig calendar (showing only shows from bands they have ‘liked’), however, we will soon be implementing a ‘news feed’ feature where we will inform your fans about all your comings and goings, news, gigs, releases etc. In the future, as our ‘fan profile’ feature develops we are confident it will become a great tool for connecting your band with the people who matter most, your fans. Please encourage your friends and fans to sign up and ‘like’ you by sharing your band’s profile with them on facebook, twitter etc.</p>

<p>We have loads of other cool new features in the works (all designed to help bands promote their music and shows to their fans), including the following :</p>

<p>- Auto export your DoIndie shows to a facebook ‘tab’ in your band’s facebook page.<br>
- A Shop to sell your merchandise / CDs and gig tickets to people not only in Korea, but all around the world<br>
- Ability to upload your music and pictures to your profile on DoIndie<br>
- DoIndie mixtapes to help fans discover new bands<br>

  - and many more.</p>

<p>
If you have any special shows coming up (like a CD release party etc), please do not hesitate to contact us as we are always happy to help promote local bands. Additionally if you have a new CD or video out coming out, please let us know. We would love to feature you in our news section <a href="http://doindie.co.kr/en/blog">http://doindie.co.kr/en/blog</a>.</p>

<p>Thanks again for using Doindie. Please tell your friends about us and help us to build this website into a long lasting pillar of the local Korean Music scene. DoIndie is always striving to develop and improve, if you have any advice, spot any mistakes on the website or want to suggest some new features to us, please drop us a message any time.</p>

